---
// Calibration — the calibration ritual.
// The 4 score bricks count up from 0 to their target. The score
// values are not just numbers; each one is a "calibrated" verdict
// that the user can read into (13 = low amount of slop, 92 = strong,
// 95 = solid, 91 = ready to ship). Below the stats, the live
// `structure.json` demo shows what the tool actually produces.
//
// v0.21.0: aiSlopScore is the raw amount of slop (lower = cleaner),
// not the inverted cleanliness reading. The 4 numbers are chosen so
// the headline reads as "this repo has low slop" rather than the
// confusing v0.20.1 "100 = clean" inversion.
import StructureDemo from './StructureDemo.astro';
---

<section class="section calibration" id="calibration">
  <header class="calibration__head">
    <span class="calibration__label">calibrated, not guessed</span>
    <h2 class="calibration__title">
      The numbers that earn the name <span class="calibration__accent">usebrick</span>.
    </h2>
  </header>

  <div class="calibration__stats">
    <div class="calibration__stat">
      <div class="calibration__value" data-target="13" data-prefix="" data-suffix="">0</div>
      <div class="calibration__axis">aiSlopScore</div>
      <div class="calibration__verdict">low amount of slop</div>
    </div>
    <div class="calibration__stat">
      <div class="calibration__value" data-target="92" data-prefix="" data-suffix="">0</div>
      <div class="calibration__axis">engineeringHygiene</div>
      <div class="calibration__verdict">strong</div>
    </div>
    <div class="calibration__stat">
      <div class="calibration__value" data-target="95" data-prefix="" data-suffix="">0</div>
      <div class="calibration__axis">security</div>
      <div class="calibration__verdict">solid</div>
    </div>
    <div class="calibration__stat">
      <div class="calibration__value" data-target="91" data-prefix="" data-suffix="">0</div>
      <div class="calibration__axis">repositoryHealth</div>
      <div class="calibration__verdict">ready to ship</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <StructureDemo />

  <blockquote class="calibration__quote">
    Every rule ships with a recall/FP ratio. A rule that fires more
    noise than signal goes back to <em>defaultOff</em> until it earns
    its way on. <strong>aiSlopScore</strong> uses the natural-reading
    direction (0 = clean, 100 = saturated) — the other three scores
    are "higher = better". v0.21.0.
    <cite class="calibration__cite">the usebrick calibration contract</cite>
  </blockquote>
</section>
